The People of the State of Illinois, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. John Lewis, Defendant-Appellant.(No. 58668;First District (3rd Division)February 21, 1974.

DEMPSEY, J., took no part.

PER CURIAM. James J. Doherty, Public Defender, of Chicago, for appellant. Bernard Carey, State’s Attorney, of Chicago (Kenneth L. Gillis and Thomas A. Manet, Assistant State’s Attorneys, of counsel), for the People.
